There's no need to join the `acs_14_5yr_b01003` table to the `ok_quakes` table -- we can simply add the population choropleth as a __new layer__, so that we can see where the big earthquakes fall in relation to the population centers:

https://modern-sql.com/feature/with

~~~sql
WITH big_ok_quakes AS (
  SELECT 
    time, mag, depth, place,
    cartodb_id, the_geom, the_geom_webmercator
  FROM ok_quakes
  WHERE mag >= 4.5
)
SELECT 
  big_ok_quakes.*
FROM big_ok_quakes
INNER JOIN ok_counties
  ON ST_WITHIN(big_ok_quakes.the_geom, ok_counties.the_geom);
~~~

